    "Inclusion Lemma, • • •, X n, Y 1, • • •, Y n ∈ Irr Z(C) and any β ∈ Z(C) X λ+1 ⊗ • • • ⊗ X λ+m → Y 1 ⊗ • • • ⊗ Y m we have Dr C C [β]P (X 1,•••,Xn) D = Dr D D [id X 1 ⊗•••⊗X λ ⊗ β ⊗ id X λ+m+1 ⊗•••⊗Xn].",
    "Proof: Let ψ = Ψ D D α ⊗ w 0 ⊗ w X 1 ⊗ • • • ⊗ w Xn for arbitrary X 0 ∈ Irr Z(C), α ∈ Z(C)(X * 0 → X 1 ⊗ • • • ⊗ X m), and w 0 ∈ C(X 0 → χ ⊗S 0).",
    "By Proposition 4.6, the range of P(X 1,•••,Xn) Dis spanned by vectors of this form.",
    "In order to compute the action of Dr C C [β] on ψ we will write ψ as a linear combination of pure tensors according to the decomposition H D = H C ⊗ H C ′.",
    "By replacing D with an equivalent anchor, we may without loss of generality assume that the anchor point of D lies in Σ C and that its attachment point to the exterior boundary component also belongs to the exterior boundary of Σ C ′."
